<br>
<br>
IF you are <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>ABLE</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to use an item, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>WILL</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> use the item, have a certain <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>NEED</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> for an item, and feel you have done enough to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>DESERVE</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the item...feel free to roll. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
We encourage people who do not feel they need an item as much, to pass on rolls. This is not something enforced but a personal judgement where we will trust to the person's integrity. I personally would like that if a person won an extremely great robe and had been using a lower grade robe,  that he/she would offer to hand down their old robe to another guildmember who was maybe runner-up and doesn't have(and also needs). The same goes for such things as Tank items. I'm sure there are many examples, but remember this isn't a rule. Also remember that such examples are remembered on future raids where most will agree you deserve an item.<br>
<br>
- We do NOT have seniority rules as this would discourage participitation(and is often considered Elitist). However again we will encourage people to pass up on loot to those who have more often contributed to the guild as a whole yet won nothing(for example Melees are likely to get nothing on a mainly caster drop raid unless they kill a random named on the way there...however the fact that they attend is, to me, worthy of recognition)<br>
<br>
<br>
Still, in alot of situations, the other systems work wonderfully for their guilds <br>
